functions.description: Search a channel's messages

parameters.name: channelID
parameters.description: The ID of the channel

parameters.name: query
parameters.description: Search parameters

parameters.name: query.sortBy
parameters.description: What to sort by, either "timestamp" or "relevance"

parameters.name: query.sortOrder
parameters.description: What order to sort by, either "asc" or "desc"

parameters.name: query.content
parameters.description: Filter results by a content string

parameters.name: query.authorID
parameters.description: Filter results by an author ID

parameters.name: query.minID
parameters.description: The minimum message ID to return results for

parameters.name: query.maxID
parameters.description: The maximum message ID to return results for

parameters.name: query.limit
parameters.description: How many messages to return, 1 <= limit <= 25

parameters.name: query.offset
parameters.description: The query index of the first message to be returned, 0 <= offset <= 5000

parameters.name: query.contextSize
parameters.description:
How many context messages around each result to return.
For example, if you searched for `6` and contextSize was 2, `[4, 5, 6, 7, 8]` would be returned

parameters.name: query.has
parameters.description: Only return messages with an "attachment", "embed", or "link"

parameters.name: query.embedProviders
parameters.description: Filter results by embed provider

parameters.name: query.embedTypes
parameters.description: Filter results by embed type

parameters.name: query.attachmentExtensions
parameters.description: Filter results by attachment extension

parameters.name: query.attachmentFilename
parameters.description: Filter results by attachment filename

returns.description:
A search result object. The object will have a `totalResults` key and `results` key.
Each entry in the result array is an array of Message objects.
In each array, the message where `Message.hit === true` is the matched message, while the other messages are context messages.
Sample return: ```
{
    totalResults: 2,
    results: [
        [Message, Message, Message (Message.hit = true), Message],
        [Message, Message, Message (Message.hit = true), Message, Message]
    ]
}
```

parameters.name: generator
parameters.description:
A response string, array of functions or strings, or function that generates a string or array of strings when called.
If a function is passed, the function will be passed a Message object and an array of command arguments. The Message object will have an additional property `prefix`, which is the prefix used in the command.
`generator(msg, args)`

parameters.name: options
parameters.description: Command options

parameters.name: options.aliases
parameters.description: An array of command aliases

parameters.name: options.caseInsensitive
parameters.description: Whether the command label (and aliases) is case insensitive or not

parameters.name: options.deleteCommand
parameters.description: Whether to delete the user command message or not

parameters.name: options.argsRequired
parameters.description: If arguments are required or not

parameters.name: options.guildOnly
parameters.description: Whether to prevent the command from being used in Direct Messages or not

parameters.name: options.dmOnly
parameters.description: Whether to prevent the command from being used in guilds or not

parameters.name: options.description
parameters.description: A short description of the command to show in the default help command

parameters.name: options.fullDescription
parameters.description: A detailed description of the command to show in the default help command

parameters.name: options.usage
parameters.description: Details on how to call the command to show in the default help command

parameters.name: options.requirements
parameters.description: A set of factors that limit who can call the command

parameters.name: options.requirements.userIDs
parameters.description: An array of user IDs representing users that can call the command

parameters.name: options.requirements.permissions
parameters.description:
An object containing permission keys the user must match to use the command
i.e.:
```
{
  "administrator": false,
  "manageMessages": true
}```
In the above example, the user must not have administrator permissions, but must have manageMessages to use the command

parameters.name: options.requirements.roleIDs
parameters.description: An array of role IDs that would allow a user to use the command

parameters.name: options.requirements.roleNames
parameters.description: An array of role names that would allow a user to use the command

parameters.name: options.cooldown
parameters.description: The cooldown between command usage in milliseconds

parameters.name: options.cooldownExclusions
parameters.description: A set of factors that limit where cooldowns are active

parameters.name: options.cooldownExclusions.userIDs
parameters.description: An array of user IDs representing users that are not affected by cooldowns.

parameters.name: options.cooldownExclusions.guildIDs
parameters.description: An array of guild IDs representing guilds that are not affected by cooldowns.

parameters.name: options.cooldownExclusions.channelIDs
parameters.description: An array of channel IDs representing channels that are not affected by cooldowns.

parameters.name: options.cooldownMessage
parameters.description: A message to show when the command is on cooldown

parameters.name: options.invalidUsageMessage
parameters.description: A message to show when a command was improperly used

parameters.name: options.permissionMessage
parameters.description: A message to show when the user doesn't have permissions to use the command

parameters.name: options.errorMessage
parameters.description: A message to show if the execution of the command handler somehow fails.

parameters.name: options.reactionButtons
parameters.description:
An array of objects specifying reaction buttons
`emoji` specifies the button emoji. Custom emojis should be in format `emojiName:emojiID`
`type` specifies the type of the reaction button, either "edit" or "cancel"
`response` specifies the content to edit the message to when the reaction button is pressed. This accepts the same arguments as the `generator` parameter of this function

parameters.name: options.reactionButtonTimeout
parameters.description: Time (in milliseconds) to wait before invalidating the command's reaction buttons

parameters.name: options.defaultSubcommandOptions
parameters.description: Default subcommand options. This object takes the same options as a normal Command

functions.description: Search a channel's messages

parameters.name: channelID
parameters.description: The ID of the channel

parameters.name: query
parameters.description: Search parameters

parameters.name: query.sortBy
parameters.description: What to sort by, either "timestamp" or "relevance"

parameters.name: query.sortOrder
parameters.description: What order to sort by, either "asc" or "desc"

parameters.name: query.content
parameters.description: Filter results by a content string

parameters.name: query.authorID
parameters.description: Filter results by an author ID

parameters.name: query.minID
parameters.description: The minimum message ID to return results for

parameters.name: query.maxID
parameters.description: The maximum message ID to return results for

parameters.name: query.limit
parameters.description: How many messages to return, 1 <= limit <= 25

parameters.name: query.offset
parameters.description: The query index of the first message to be returned, 0 <= offset <= 5000

parameters.name: query.contextSize
parameters.description:
How many context messages around each result to return.
For example, if you searched for `6` and contextSize was 2, `[4, 5, 6, 7, 8]` would be returned

parameters.name: query.has
parameters.description: Only return messages with an "attachment", "embed", or "link"

parameters.name: query.embedProviders
parameters.description: Filter results by embed provider

parameters.name: query.embedTypes
parameters.description: Filter results by embed type

parameters.name: query.attachmentExtensions
parameters.description: Filter results by attachment extension

parameters.name: query.attachmentFilename
parameters.description: Filter results by attachment filename

returns.description:
A search result object. The object will have a `totalResults` key and `results` key.
Each entry in the result array is an array of Message objects.
In each array, the message where `Message.hit === true` is the matched message, while the other messages are context messages.
Sample return: ```
{
    totalResults: 2,
    results: [
        [Message, Message, Message (Message.hit = true), Message],
        [Message, Message, Message (Message.hit = true), Message, Message]
    ]
}
```
